  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nBoth the `VM` and `State` (aka `VMState`) objects implement a `block_class` or (`_block_class` from the `VM`) property and API.  There should only be one `block_class` defined for a given VM ruleset.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\n- Remove the `block_class` API from the `VM` class and change all usage to delegate to the `State` class API.\r\n- Change the `State` class to have a `get_block_class()` which is a `classmethod` for retrieval of the class instead of directly accessing it via the attribute.",
